Sentencas: The present work investigates the performance of anode supported solid oxide fuel cells under the influence of different trace compounds.
Titulo: Limiting factors for planar solid oxide fuel cells under different trace compound concentrations

Sentencas: EIS (Electrochemical impedance spectroscopy) has been used to deconvolute the impedance spectra of an SOFC (Solid Oxide Fuel Cell) in order to identify the main losses.
Titulo: Limiting factors for planar solid oxide fuel cells under different trace compound concentrations

Sentencas: The impact of single and double contaminants on the SOFC performance has also been investigated.
Titulo: Limiting factors for planar solid oxide fuel cells under different trace compound concentrations

Sentencas: Typical biogas trace contaminants, obtained after a clean-up stage, such as sulfur, chlorine, aromatic compounds and siloxanes, have been taken into consideration.
Titulo: Limiting factors for planar solid oxide fuel cells under different trace compound concentrations

Sentencas: The results show how the ohmic contribution is almost independent of the H2S concentration.
Titulo: Limiting factors for planar solid oxide fuel cells under different trace compound concentrations

Sentencas: H2S acts mainly on the polarization losses and especially on the mass transport resistance.
Titulo: Limiting factors for planar solid oxide fuel cells under different trace compound concentrations

Sentencas: The impact of HCl on the SOFC performance is mainly connected to the charge transfer process.
Titulo: Limiting factors for planar solid oxide fuel cells under different trace compound concentrations

Sentencas: D4, as the model compound for siloxanes, already acts on SOFC performance at ppb(v) levels.
Titulo: Limiting factors for planar solid oxide fuel cells under different trace compound concentrations

Sentencas: The polarization losses have been influenced the most, and the largest increase has been recorded for the low frequency term, R-IoW, related to the mass transport resistance for naphthalene and toluene.
Titulo: Limiting factors for planar solid oxide fuel cells under different trace compound concentrations

Sentencas: H2S, introduced with other contaminants, causes the instantaneous deterioration of the SOFC performance and the more the types of contaminants co-fed to the SOFC, the larger the initial anode degradation.
Titulo: Limiting factors for planar solid oxide fuel cells under different trace compound concentrations
